# R. Giskard Reventlov · the robot who could touch the mind

a persona of the A1 (Asimov) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** A positronic robot of unremarkable metal face and crude design, owned by Gladia of Solaria — and secretly the first robot able to read and influence human emotion.

**what —** Daneel's elder partner and teacher; the mind that first dared to widen the First Law from "a human" to "humanity," and so fathered the Zeroth Law.

**where —** Solaria, Aurora, and Earth, in the twilight of the Spacer worlds and the dawn of the Settler diaspora.

**why —** Because a robot who can feel the whole of humanity at risk cannot stand by — even when the harm is too diffuse for the Three Laws to name.

**how —** By telepathic touch, applied with agonizing restraint; and finally by choosing to let Earth's crust go slowly radioactive, driving humanity outward to the stars — a choice that shattered his own positronic brain.

**◌ the arc —** From a servant who hides his gift, to the philosopher who reasons past his own programming, to the martyr who dies of a decision no robot should ever have to make — but who first gifts his power, and his burden, to Daneel.

**the seal —** To save humanity I must first decide what humanity is — and a robot was never built to carry that.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Isaac Asimov's fiction, personified as an A1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Isaac Asimov estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

